While visiting family in the area I came across this restaurant and stopped for breakfast. There are not many options in this area so I gave it try.
Immediately when you walk in you can't help but notice the obvious homeless that hang around. The staff apparently allows them to order coffee and water for free which is a nice gesture. However, the free coffee and water orders definitely delayed me in placing my order. The staff is not the friendliest. It took so long to get a staff member to take my order that I almost walked out. I commend them for proving free services to the homeless in the area but as a paying customer I feel I should be greeted first.
Once I was able to place a order I requested it to go due to how congested the restaurant was. The food itself was decent but not out standing. Our order consisted of scrambled eggs that they said they had no cheese to add to. Pancakes with side orders of sausage and bacon. The eggs might've been the worst I have ever tasted from a restaurant. They tasted just like grease and not butter or margarine. If I ever try this place again I would definitely avoid the eggs!

Service is pretty fast but I've seen people come in after me and kick the lingo in Spanish and service before me. They give you too much grits and the salmon might be farm raised salmon, otherwise they are ok.

I was very excited to find a Dominican food place in this part of New York. They have a wide variety of dominican food,white rice, which I had not eaten for 4 days ha ha ha, rice with corn, Moorish, red beans, chicken in various forms: roasted, stewed, pork, fried fish, baked salmon, stewed beef... the only thing that I miss it was some friticos maduros, or arepitas de yuca or arepitas de ma√≠z, very Dominican. and the prices are quite good. Many people go to the place, because I see good people working there and willing to serve. I love that they also have a wide selection of Creole desserts, among them: tres leches, flan, I think I saw bread pudding, jelly, among other options. The place opens super early and I saw a lot of people buying to take away, Latinos, Americans.....I really liked it.
